HEADWORD: Exinanite
<hw>Ex*in"a*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exinanitus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exinanire</ets>; <ets>ex</ets> out
(intens.) + <ets>inanire</ets> to make empty, <ets>inanis</ets>,
empty.]</ety> <def>To make empty; to render of no effect; to
humble.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Pearson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

